Interface QueryDimInterface

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DicooglePlugin, QueryInterface

    public interface QueryDimInterface
extends QueryInterface
    Query Interface provides methods to query at different levels in DICOM Information Model. Created by bastiao on 02-02-2017.

    • Method Detail

      • queryPatient

        java.lang.Iterable<? extends PatientInterface> queryPatient(java.lang.String query,
                                                            java.lang.Object... parameters)
                                                     throws QueryException
        Performs a search on the database. The consumer of the results would either request an iterator or use a for-each loop. The underlying iterator implementation can be redefined to wait for more results at the caller. Furthermore, the resulting iterable is expected to be traversed only once.
        Parameters:
        query - a string describing the query. The underlying plugin is currently free to follow any query format, but only those based on Lucene with work with the search user interface.
        parameters - A variable list of parameters of the query. The plugin can use them to establish their own API's, which may require more complex data structures (e.g. images).
        Returns:
        the results of the query as a (possibly lazy) iterable with Patient
        Throws:
        QueryException

      • query

        java.lang.Iterable<SearchResult> query(java.lang.String query,
                                       DimLevel level,
                                       java.lang.Object... parameters)
                                throws QueryException
        Performs a search on the database.
        Parameters:
        query - a string describing the query. The underlying plugin is currently free to follow any query format.
        level - a level of the query, for instance, Patient, Study, Series or Instance
        parameters - A variable list of parameters of the query. The plugin can use them to establish their own API's, which may require more complex data structures (e.g. images).
        Returns:
        the results of the query as a (possibly lazy) iterable
        Throws:
        QueryException
